"children":[
"Obesity"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s36_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s36_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"41a805",
"children":[
"Waist circumference ≥102 cm (40 in) in men and ≥88 cm (35 in) in women correlates with visceral adiposity and increased risk for diabetes, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"cardiovascular disease",
"children":[
"CVD"
]
},
","
]
},
" and all-cause mortality."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6e1f73",
"children":[
"Laboratory evaluation should include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c617c0",
"children":[
"thyroid and liver function"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"269938",
"children":[
"lipid levels"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"73742f",
"children":[
"screening for diabetes"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a7f77d",
"children":[
"Cancer screening recommendations are the same as for patients without obesity. Screening for CVD is reserved for symptomatic patients."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s36_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"50a200",
"children":[
"Treatment options include lifestyle modification, pharmacotherapy, and bariatric surgery. A reasonable initial goal is weight loss of 0.5 kg to 1.0 kg/week (1.1-2.2 lb) to achieve a total weight loss of 10%."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c8a80e",
"children":[
"A specific daily calorie limit should be prescribed (typically, 1500-1800 kcal/d for men and 1200-1500 kcal/d for women). All diets are equally effective. Exercise ≥150 min/week is helpful as an adjunct to diet change but not effective as monotherapy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b02501",
"children":[
"Pharmacologic therapy may be used as adjunctive therapy in patients with a ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"body mass index",
"children":[
"BMI"
]
},
" ≥30 or in patients with a BMI ≥27 and weight-associated comorbidities."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s36_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"06e975",
"children":[
"Bariatric surgery is considered for patients with a BMI ≥40 and for patients with a BMI ≥35 with serious obesity-related comorbidities (severe sleep apnea, diabetes, severe joint disease)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5658f4",
"children":[
"Bariatric surgery outcomes are associated with:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6c8715",
"children":[
"improved control or remission of type 2 diabetes"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b9ecac",
"children":[
"improved quality of life"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"36046b",
"children":[
"reduced medication use"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bbd790",
"children":[
"reduced mortality"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4c96fb",
"children":[
"Commonly performed bariatric procedures include laparoscopic adjustable gastric banding, Roux-en-Y gastric bypass, and sleeve gastrectomy."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s36_inline_t3"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
